threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This MIPSEL ELF binary is a variant of the Mirai IoT botnet, specifically the Rebirth variant. It is designed to infect embedded devices (like routers) and incorporate them into a DDoS network. Key malicious behaviors include targeting a Huawei TR-064 vulnerability (DeviceUpgrade_1) via hardcoded SOAP exploit payloads, system-wide process enumeration via /proc to identify and terminate competing botnets, and multiple specialized DDoS attack modules (TCP, UDP, and VSE floods). The binary includes references to a known malicious infrastructure 'bigbins.rebirth.st' and utilizes a local instance killer mechanism using the magic value 0xda00eb1c to ensure single execution.
